<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>I think it is more and more becoming clear that google's approach is the best way: your ideal first page has to be personalized (when you are looged in, Google personalizes your results with location, previous searches, +1s, and even who you follow on twitter).<p>Trying to be everything to everybody means there will be people left with sub-optimal results.</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=200></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3167073 href="vote?for=3167073&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%5a%76%6a%53%59%37%66%4a%75%43"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3167073></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=keeperofdakeys">keeperofdakeys</a> 100 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3167073">link</a></span></div><br>
