<span class="comment"><font color=#000000>The real problem your honey-pot suggestion has is that there is a diversity of opinions and expertise across the site, and it's not the case that they're easily separable.<p>Should you discount someone's technical opinion because they are vocal about their political opinion?  Because that's essentially what your system would do.  And it would do so without notifying them that this was occurring.</font></span><p><font size=1><font color=#f6f6ef>-----</font></font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table border=0><tr><td><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/s.gif" height=1 width=200></td><td valign=top><center><a id=up_3168464 href="vote?for=3168464&dir=up&whence=%2f%78%3f%66%6e%69%64%3d%5a%76%6a%53%59%37%66%4a%75%43"><img src="http://ycombinator.com/images/grayarrow.gif" border=0 vspace=3 hspace=2></a><span id=down_3168464></span></center></td><td class="default"><div style="margin-top:2px; margin-bottom:-10px; "><span class="comhead"><a href="user?id=pbhjpbhj">pbhjpbhj</a> 100 days ago  | <a href="item?id=3168464">link</a></span></div><br>
